wikipedia_page.main: Willie Aspinall (8 November 1942 – 23 October 2021) was a professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1960s and 1970s. He played at representative level for Great Britain, and at club level for Warrington (Heritage No. 631), and Rochdale Hornets, as a stand-off
